headline: Shareholder Proposal Urges Vote Against Target (NYSE:TGT) Chair Over Living Wage Issues
summary: Target (NYSE:TGT) has recently been at the center of discussions regarding corporate governance as The Shareholder Commons, Inc. urged shareholders to vote against Chair Brian C. Cornell due to concerns over wage practices. Parallel to this, Target expanded its product range by launching an exclusive line of eco-friendly cleaning products with Branch Basics. Despite these developments, Target's stock price remained flat over the past week, moving less than 1%. Meanwhile, the broader market...
